        "label": "Producer (nats-latest)",
        "description": "Opens a Data/Out channel `frames` whose declared transport is `nats-latest` — lossy-latest core NATS, NOT the durable JetStream default. After a brief lead-in (so the consumer can connect — core NATS has no replay), it paces 20 small binary frames over the out-of-band transport, one every ~150 ms. The compiler bakes `transport: nats-latest` into the manifest; the SDK stamps it into the channel's `open` descriptor; the producer's executor dispatches the lossy publish adapter off it. Zero SDK change — same `open_output(...).write(...)` as every other data demo.",
        "channels": [
          {
            "name": "frames",
            "direction": "out",
