        "type": "automated_step",
        "label": "Consumer (unchanged stream())",
        "description": "Declares a Data/In channel `frames` wired from the producer's open handle and drains it via the ORDINARY `for frame in aithericon.stream('frames')` API — completely unaware that the bytes rode lossy core NATS instead of JetStream. The consumer's executor lifts `transport` from the producer's `open` descriptor and dispatches the matching subscribe adapter. This is the proof: one producer/consumer SDK, two transports, selected by data. Lossy means a late/slow consumer MAY miss early frames — so `received` can be < `sent` (that is the contract, not a bug).",
        "channels": [
